oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Sewing club on the front porch of a house
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Group shot of a sewing club on the front porch of a house on Washington Avenue which was owned by Mr. and Mrs. Rutledge Smith. Young girls are dressed up and are holding sewing materials and tools.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Sewing; Sewing equipment & supplies; Children; Porches; Houses; Clothing & dress; Clubs
